The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Tuesday, August 03, 2004 				 Drowning in search of ball
																								Calcutta, Aug. 2: Arkadeb Bhattacharya, 23, drowned this evening when he went to fetch a football from a pond in Behalas Parnasree.																								Bhattacharya was playing a friendly match when the ball fell in the pond next to the ground around 5.30 pm. He was not the only one trying to retrieve the ball that floated to the middle. When the rest realised that he was missing, police were called. Divers of the force found the body past midnight. 																								In a separate incident, the bodies of Akash, 4, and Batash Das, 5, were found floating in a canal in Baduria. The police said they possibly fell into the water while playing.
